---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import LegalPage from "../components/LegalPage.astro";
import { getBrandEmail } from "../lib/site";

const brandEmail = getBrandEmail();
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Refund and Cancellation Policy"
  description="Refund and cancellation policy for Tactas AI task reviews, implementation work, and ongoing managed AI agent plans."
  canonical="/refund-policy"
  currentPath="/refund-policy"
  navbarTheme="light"
  navbarCtaLabel="Book a review"
>
  <LegalPage title="Refund and Cancellation Policy" updatedAt="May 28, 2026">
    <section>
      <h2 class="legal-section-title text-lg font-semibold">Overview</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">
        Tactas AI provides consulting, implementation, and managed operation services for AI agents and workflow
        automation systems. Refund and cancellation terms may also be specified in signed proposals, statements of work,
        or service agreements. If those documents conflict with this policy, the signed agreement controls.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="legal-section-title text-lg font-semibold">Task reviews and implementation work</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">
        Fees for task reviews, discovery, planning, implementation, integration, configuration, testing, and other
        project work are refundable only before work begins, unless a signed agreement states otherwise.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        Once work has started, fees for completed work, time spent, reserved delivery capacity, and third-party costs
        already incurred are non-refundable. If a project is cancelled before all milestones are delivered, Tactas AI may
        refund unused prepaid amounts for work that has not started, after deducting completed work and incurred costs.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="legal-section-title text-lg font-semibold">Ongoing managed plans</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">
        Monthly ongoing plans may be cancelled at any time by contacting Tactas AI. Cancellation stops future renewals,
        but the current billing period remains active through its paid term.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        Monthly plan fees are not prorated or refunded for partial billing periods, except where required by law or where
        Tactas AI approves a refund for a billing error, duplicate charge, unauthorized charge, or material failure to
        provide the paid service.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="legal-section-title text-lg font-semibold">Third-party costs</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">
        Fees charged by third-party platforms, vendors, software providers, payment processors, hosting services,
        messaging providers, API providers, data vendors, or integration partners are not refundable by Tactas AI unless
        Tactas AI directly controls the charge and receives a corresponding refund from the provider.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="legal-section-title text-lg font-semibold">How to request a refund or cancellation</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">
        To request a refund or cancellation, email <a class="legal-link" href={`mailto:${brandEmail}`}>{brandEmail}</a>
        with your business name, invoice or payment details, and the reason for the request. Refund requests should be
        submitted within 14 days of the relevant charge.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        Tactas AI reviews requests in good faith and normally responds within 5 business days. Approved refunds are
        returned to the original payment method when possible and may take additional time to appear depending on the
        payment processor or bank.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="legal-section-title text-lg font-semibold">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">
        Tactas AI may update this policy as services, billing models, or legal requirements change. The updated version
        will be posted on this page with a revised effective date.
      </p>
    </section>
  </LegalPage>
</BaseLayout>
